@trevor-m thanks for making the changes, I'll take a look soon. Please add the mnist test case, it's fine to include test data as long as it's not too big.

@aaroey
I have implemented all of your requested changes and I am just finishing up the tests. However I am getting this error with the MNIST test. Have you encountered this before? I suspect it has to do with how bazel is executing the test...

2018-11-09 00:41:44.473973: E tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/convert/convert_graph.cc:660] Node construction failed withInvalid argument: Op type not registered 'TRTEngineOp' in binary running on 8eb481f0e4e9. Make sure the Op and Kernel are registered in the binary running in this process. Note that if you are loading a saved graph which used ops from tf.contrib, accessing (e.g.) `tf.contrib.resampler` should be done before importing the graph, as contrib ops are lazily registered when the module is first accessed. while building NodeDef 'my_trt_op_0'
